new treatment has been discovered and they have&nbsp;
room for Sarah. Anna is skeptical since she never&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:34.480 --> 00:01:38.720
heard of it from their doctor, Mathieu explains&nbsp;
it's new and it hasn't been published yet. They'd&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:38.720 --> 00:01:43.440
just need to move to Canada, which Anna doesn't&nbsp;
like. She thinks Mathieu is complicating things,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:47.200
they've already been lucky enough to get&nbsp;
Sarah out of the hospital and she has a life.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:51.280
But Mathieu doesn't think that's a life.
Meanwhile, Sarah is having a videocall&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:55.280
with some friends that have the same condition as&nbsp;
here, including a girl named Charlotte and Sarah's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:55.280 --> 00:02:00.560
crush, NoÃ©, who refers to their little group as&nbsp;
"goldfishes in a tank". Back to Mathieu and Anna,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:04.560
they're still discussing this new treatment.&nbsp;
Mathieu wants Anna to think about it, Anna&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:08.720
says they can go when there are real results,&nbsp;
but Mathieu replies it must be decided now.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:12.400
He wants these doctors to get Sarah out&nbsp;
of the capsule so he can finally hug her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:16.160
Anna asks for more time, so Mathieu leaves&nbsp;
the apartment and returns to his own.&nbsp;

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:20.560
While Sarah continues to chat with her&nbsp;
friends, the tv shows important news:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:24.640
an earthquake of a magnitude never seen&nbsp;
before has isolated Sweden and Denmark.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:24.640 --> 00:02:28.320
Mathieu hears this from the shower, and it's&nbsp;
at that exact moment that an earthquake hits&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:28.320 --> 00:02:33.120
Paris as well. The power suddenly goes out&nbsp;
and Sarah's capsule changes to battery mode.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:37.040
She calls her dad, who is hurrying to&nbsp;
get dressed, to ask what's going on.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:41.440
Mathieu tells her he'll be over soon. When he&nbsp;
makes out he hears alarms and sees people running&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:46.480
on the streets. Sarah tries to contact him again,&nbsp;
he tells her she and her mom should stay put.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:46.480 --> 00:02:50.640
He walks down the street and, after noticing&nbsp;
a flock of birds desperately flying away,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:54.560
he finally finds the problem: there is a thick&nbsp;
mist coming out of the ground and killing anyone&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:59.120
that breathes it. It is expanding and taking&nbsp;
over the city, so Mathieu immediately starts&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:04.320
running back to his family. Once inside, he finds&nbsp;
Anna by the window so he quickly drags her away,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:08.400
telling her not to breathe the mist. To Sarah,&nbsp;
he says that they'll have to leave her there,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:12.560
but promises they'll come back for her soon.
As the mist also makes its way up inside the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:12.560 --> 00:03:16.640
building, Mathieu and Anna rush upstairs until&nbsp;
they make it to the highest apartment where an&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:20.960
elderly couple, Lucien and Colette, live.&nbsp;
Lucien lets them in and Mathieu runs to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:25.520
the window to check on the fog: it has stopped&nbsp;
at roof level. Mathieu then asks for some rags&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:30.160
which he uses to cover the spacer under the door&nbsp;
while Anna contacts Sarah with the walkie-talkie.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:30.160 --> 00:03:34.480
Sarah tells them the fog has invaded her room&nbsp;
but she's fine because the capsule protects her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:38.800
Afterward, both couples go out to the balcony to&nbsp;
look at the city, which is now completely covered&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:43.760
by the mist, leaving only the rooftops visible.&nbsp;
Colette gets scared, so her husband comforts her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:48.320
by saying their son is fine and takes her back&nbsp;
inside. Mathieu and Anna wonder if the fog is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:48.320 --> 00:03:53.040
toxic and where it came from, and they see two&nbsp;
helicopters fly by. They decide to also return&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:57.920
inside before the fog kills them. In the capsule,&nbsp;
Sarah watches the fog get thicker around her.&nbsp;

00:03:58.640 --> 00:04:02.160
Back in the apartment, Lucien and Colette&nbsp;
are checking their food while Anna looks at&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:07.360
the capsule battery on her phone app. There are&nbsp;
four bars left, which Sarah confirms on her side.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:07.360 --> 00:04:12.240
This means she still has ten hours of battery.&nbsp;
While they chat, Mathieu finds some binoculars,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:15.760
which he hangs on his shoulder as he goes out&nbsp;
to the balcony and climbs the wall to reach&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:15.760 --> 00:04:21.200
the rooftop. There he uses the binoculars to look&nbsp;
farther at the city: the mist truly is everywhere.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:24.240
He returns to the balcony to find&nbsp;
Lucien trying to use his phone,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:28.400
but there is still no signal. His son&nbsp;
lives two blocks from there on a low floor,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:32.720
but he's smart so Lucien is sure he's safe.&nbsp;
Colette shows up then, saying they should go&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:38.000
visit their son, and Lucien has to remind her&nbsp;
of the mist. She has memory problems. They all&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:42.240
go back inside and after she ends her talk&nbsp;
with Sarah, Anna asks Mathieu for an update,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:46.960
but he hasn't seen any rescue teams. Anna&nbsp;
is worried about the capsule battery life.&nbsp;

00:04:46.960 --> 00:04:51.600
Meanwhile, Lucien searches his closet to find&nbsp;
an old radio and brings it over to the table.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:54.880
While the others take a look at it, Lucien&nbsp;
goes out to the hallway to check the fog.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:55.440 --> 00:05:00.000
He puts his hand in it and nothing happens, he&nbsp;
sniffs his fingers after but there's no smell.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.480
He decides to go back inside, where Anna is&nbsp;
working on the radio because it doesn't work.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:08.320
Mathieu wants to go check on Sarah, Anna points&nbsp;
out he wouldn't be able to hold his breath for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:13.120
so long. An idea comes to Mathieu then: he&nbsp;
remembers Mr. Belkacem and his oxygen tank.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:16.880
He could hold his breath long enough to&nbsp;
get the tank then visit Sarah freely,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:16.880 --> 00:05:20.400
since he is only living one floor&nbsp;
under it. Mathieu opens the window,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:24.080
gets a hammer and flashlight from Lucien&nbsp;
and some tape from a drawer and climbs out,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:24.080 --> 00:05:28.800
taking a deep breath before entering the fog.
When he makes it to Mr. Belkacem's, he enters&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:28.800 --> 00:05:32.560
it after breaking the window with the hammer&nbsp;
and starts looking around with the flashlight.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:36.720
First he finds Mr. Belkacem's body on the floor,&nbsp;
and his search thankfully comes to end quickly&nbsp;&nbsp;

