00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:53.200
the walkie-talkies. Sarah is worried about her&nbsp;
dad, Anna tells her to do her exercises and starts&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:53.200 --> 00:06:57.600
guiding her through them when Mathieu arrives. As&nbsp;
the elders come closer, he tells everyone about&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:57.600 --> 00:07:01.760
what he found and informs them they'll have to&nbsp;
spend the night there. He also asks Anna if she&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:06.720
wants to go see Sarah, but she's against the idea:&nbsp;
she'd rather save the oxygen for an emergency.&nbsp;

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:10.560
Later at night, Anna continues to work on&nbsp;
the radio while Lucien and Colette ask her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:14.240
questions about Sarah's illness, remembering the&nbsp;
day the family arrived at the building with the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:14.240 --> 00:07:19.040
big capsule. Meanwhile, Mathieu goes out to the&nbsp;
hallway once again to check on the fog and notices&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:23.920
it's raising. He makes a mark on the wall with the&nbsp;
time to keep track of it. He goes back inside as&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:28.800
the elders are leaving for bed, and after Anna&nbsp;
asks, he tells her about the mist going up. They&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:33.520
realized services aren't coming back soon and&nbsp;
it'll only get worse from now on. Mathieu goes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:38.640
to sleep, but Anna can't. So she decides to visit&nbsp;
a sleeping Sarah after all, and takes the chance&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:38.640 --> 00:07:42.800
to change the capsule battery before leaving.
