but Mathieu puts on the mask and pushes him off&nbsp;
the edge of the platform. They fall on top of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:30.240 --> 00:11:34.640
car and struggle for control, the officer tries&nbsp;
to get off Mathieu to reach his gun but Mathieu&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:34.640 --> 00:11:38.720
grabs him from behind and keeps him with him long&nbsp;
enough for the fog to have its effect on him.&nbsp;

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:43.040
Back in the apartment, Sarah and Anna are once&nbsp;
again chatting through the walkie-talkies.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:43.040 --> 00:11:47.280
Sarah asks if there's anything after death and&nbsp;
that she believes things can't just end here.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:47.280 --> 00:11:51.040
Anna mentions she's a scientist so she&nbsp;
can't believe the fog is divine or magic,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:55.360
it must be a reaction to something. Their talk is&nbsp;
interrupted when Anna's phone alerts her that the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:55.360 --> 00:11:59.440
capsule battery is running out. After a quick&nbsp;
look at Mathieu running through the streets,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:59.440 --> 00:12:03.040
we see Anna getting ready to go change the&nbsp;
capsule battery, which is dangerous but she&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:03.040 --> 00:12:07.520
has no other choice since there are only ten&nbsp;
minutes left. Lucien offers to go himself,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:07.520 --> 00:12:12.080
since he thinks it's fine if a man his age doesn't&nbsp;
make it back, but Anna refuses. After another&nbsp;&nbsp;

